description.p:
chemical vapor depositing a layer of silicon atop a substrate within a chemical vapor deposition reactor at a selected temperature and at a selected pressure;


without removing the substrate from the reactor after providing the silicon layer, and without exposing the substrate to surface cleaning conditions within the reactor after providing the silicon layer, in situ exposing the silicon layer to oxidizing conditions within the reactor effective to grow a layer of silicon dioxide to a thickness of at least 5 Angstroms; and


without removing the substrate from the reactor after the oxidizing step, in situ chemical vapor depositing a layer of hemispherical grain polysilicon over the silicon dioxide layer.
